snippet.textDisplay:
Hollywood Rampant with Child Abuse
Perhaps Americans should take celebrity whistleblowers like Corey Feldman and Elijah Wood more seriously when they speak about systemic pedophilia in Hollywood.

Elijah Wood famously said in an interview,

“You all grew up with Savile – Jesus, it must have been devastating. Clearly something major was going on in Hollywood. It was all organized. There are a lot of vipers in this industry, people who only have their own interests in mind. People with parasitic interests will see you as their prey. There is a darkness in the underbelly – if you can imagine it, it’s probably happened. Victims can’t speak as loudly as people in power. That’s the tragedy of attempting to reveal what is happening to innocent people. They can be squashed but their lives have been irreparably damaged.”

Anne Henry, co-founder of Bizparents, an organization with the purpose of helping child actors, said Hollywood is currently sheltering approximately 100 active abusers.

Amy Berg’s documentary An Open Secret revealed the full scope of the problem, and was completely squashed by the Establishment after its premiere.

It was only shown in nine theaters in Denver and Seattle starting on June 5th, 2015, and was quickly removed.

It eventually got distribution by cutting it from an R to a PG-13 rating, long after the “buzz” had worn off.

However, it now seems to be impossible to find, except through bootleg copies on YouTube
